Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reportRouteTypeConstraints(25.10)            reportRouteTypeConstraints(25.10)

Name
       reportRouteTypeConstraints  -  Reports  the route type constraints that
       are being added on nets during the Innovus flow

Syntax
       reportRouteTypeConstraints

       [-help]

       [-file <fileName>]

       [-svr]

       [-svrOnly]

       [-threshold value]

       [-summary  | -detailed ] [-detailed  [-timing ]]

       Reports the route type constraints that are being added on nets  during
       the  Innovus  flow. It allows you to monitor the number of constraints,
       the preferred bottom layer used, the adherence of  the  different  con-
       straint  type by the router, and the type of non-default rule (NDR) be-
       ing used.

       The command extracts information about the following  groups  of  route
       type constraints:

              * INNOVUS:  includes all route types being added by the software
                and that are using a bottom preferred layer  and  the  default
                rule.

              * INNOVUS_NDR: includes all route types being added by the soft-
                ware and that are using an NDR.

                setOptMode  -opt_pre_route_ndr_aware  makes  this type of con-
                straint.

              *

                INNOVUS_CLK: includes all route types of clock nets  that  are
                being added by the software and that are using default rule.

                create_route_type without -non_default_rule and ccopt_property
                route_type make this type of constraint.

              *

                INNOVUS_CLK_NDR:  include  all  route types of clock nets that
                are being added by the software and that are using an NDR.

                create_route_type with  -non_default_rule  and  ccopt_property
                route_type make this type of constraint.

              * USER:  includes  all route types being added by the user. This
                can be done using the setAttribute command.

              * USER_NDR: includes all route types being added by the user and
                that are using an NDR. This can be done using the setAttribute
                command.

       When via pillar report is enabled, using the -svr/-svrOnly  parameters,
       the  command  checks  via pillar assigned on data/clock nets and on the
       secondary PG nets. For sample reports, see Use Model Scenarios.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation  for  each reportRouteTypeConstraints parameter. For a
              detailed description of the command and all of  its  parameters,
              use the  man command:

               man reportRouteTypeConstraints

       -detailed
              Prints  detailed  information on each net with a route type con-
              straint such as the wire length,  the  routing  adherence,  some
              timing information, and so on.

              Note: The parameters, -detailed and -summary are mutually exclu-
              sive.

       -file file<Name>
              Specifies the file name in which the results will be written. If
              this  parameter is not specified, the information is written out
              in the console and the log file.

       -svr   When specified, reports pins with stack via rule constraints.

       -svrOnly
              When specified, reports only those pins that have stack via rule
              constraints.

       -summary
              Prints a summary of the layer constraint usage  per  layer,  per
              NDR, and per constraint type.

              Note: The parameters, -detailed and -summary are mutually exclu-
              sive.

       -threshold <value>
              Specifies the maximum routing adherence for a net to be included
              in  detailed  report. This parameter is specified along with the
              -detailed paramater.

              The default value is 80, which means only nets with adherence  <
              80 % will be included in detailed report.

              Note:  It is recommended that you do not  use the -threshold pa-
              rameter along with the -svrOnly parameter because stack via rule
              has no "routing adherence ratio" metric.

       -timing
              When this parameter is specified, the report will display timing
              information on the nets such as slack,  delay,  and  incremental
              delay while generating the detailed information.

Use Model Scenarios
       The  use  model  scenarios for reports including via pillar constraints
       applied on secondary PG pins are provided below.

