Examples
              * The following command prints the summary for  the  route  type
                constraints:

                reportRouteTypeConstraints -summary

                The  report  below  summarizes  the  number of route type con-
                straints per layer  for each category.

              * The report below summarizes the  number  of  route  type  con-
                straints  per  NDR  and  for each category. The syntax used is
                categories_NDR name.

              * The following command prints  the  detailed  route  type  con-
                straints information:

                reportRouteTypeConstraints -detailed

                The   report   below   summarizes the percentage of respect of
                the route type constraint (bottom preferred layer) by the cur-
                rent router. For example, in the report below, for the INNOVUS
                constraints between 90% and 100% respect  of  the  constraint,
                there  are  100.0%  of the nets. While INNOVUS_CLK constraints
                between 90 - 100% respect of the constraint, there are  98.33%
                of the nets.

                The  report  below summarizes the percentage of respect of the
                NDR constraint by the current router. For example, in the  re-
                port  below,  for  the INNOVUS_NDR constraints between 90% and
                100% respect of the constraint, there are 100% of the nets.

                The report below provides information similar to above reports
                but on a net to net basis.

              * The following command prints  the  detailed  route  type  con-
                straints  information  with specified threshold routing adher-
                ence of 101, which means only nets with adherence < 101 % will
                be included in detailed report.

                reportRouteTypeConstraints -detailed  -threshold 101

                A part of the sample report is shown below.

              * The following command prints information about the  layer  as-
                signment, NDR, and stack via rule.

                reportRouteTypeConstraints -svr

